---
title: Creamy Salmon and Leek Stew with buttery rice
description: With leeks, carrots and salmon all featured, this creamy stew manages to strike the perfect balance between hearty and light. Fresh thyme adds an earthiness while a bed of buttery rice adds a little bit of richness to a wonderfully rounded meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF_Y24_R15_W32_IE_IEXCF20074-3_MAIN_high-60f6e742.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipecards/card/664f2d208606e082f188772d-en-IE.pdf
author: HelloFresh
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: European
nutrition:
  calories: 734 kcal
  fat: 30.9 g
  saturated fat: 11.3 g
  carbohydrates: 87.1 g
  sugar: 9.9 g
  protein: 31.1 g
  fiber: 0.1 g
  sodium: 1.9 g
  serving size: 467
source: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipes/creamy-salmon-and-leek-stew-664f2d208606e082f188772d
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Add @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) to a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting
lid. Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover, and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve
(the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, remove the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1%unit}.
Halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways.

Trim the @carrot{1%unit}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop
widthways into small pieces.

Place a separate #large pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, cook the carrot and leek until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pick the @thyme{5%g}(leaves picked, stalks discarded). Add the thyme,
@vegetable stock{1%sachet} and @water{100%ml} (double for 4p). Cover and
simmer until the veg is tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat the @salmon{200%g}(diced) to remove excess moisture. IMPORTANT:
Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish. Season with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> Fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once the veg is cooked, add the @creme fraiche{110%g} and mix well to combine.

Scatter the salmon cubes over the stew. Cover and cook for another
~{4-5%minutes}.

Quarter the @lemon{1%unit}. Taste the stew and season with salt and pepper. Add
a splash of @water{to taste} if you feel it's too thick.

Stir a knob of @butter{to taste} through the rice, fluffing it up as you go.
Divide between plates.

Top with the leek and salmon stew. Add a squeeze of lemon. Serve any remaining
lemon wedges on the side.

> With leeks, carrots and salmon all featured, this creamy stew manages to strike
> the perfect balance between hearty and light. Fresh thyme adds an earthiness
> while a bed of buttery rice adds a little bit of richness to a wonderfully
> rounded meal.